Manchester United been dumped out of Champions League by Atletico Madrid. Renan Lodi’s first-half header gave Atletico Madrid a 1-0 victory away to Manchester United on Tuesday that sent the Spanish side through to the Champions League quarter-finals 2-1 on aggregate. The Brazilian scored just before half-time in the second leg at Old Trafford to leave United facing a fifth consecutive season without a trophy. More to follow… (SOURCE: The24)